{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013tsTKC97m1aZdYZX1kdp31","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Everything looks good. Now I need to:\n\n1. **Phase 1: 5.0 → 6.0**\n   - Upgrade secondaries first (mongodb-replica-2, then mongodb-replica-1)\n   - Step down primary, then upgrade mongodb-replica-0\n   - Verify RS health\n   - Set FCV to 6.0\n\n2. **Phase 2: 6.0 → 7.0**\n   - Same process but with mongo:7.0.5 image\n   - Set FCV to 7.0\n\nFor the upgrade, I need to update the StatefulSet image. \n\nI can use the partition field in the rolling update strategy to control which pods get updated first. I'll set the partition to 2 so only the secondary replicas get the new image initially, then gradually lower it to update the primary last. This ensures MongoDB's replica set stays healthy throughout the upgrade since secondaries can be updated without affecting availability. pod-2 updates first since it has the highest ordinal, then I'll verify it's healthy before moving to pod-1 with partition=1, and finally step down the primary pod-0 to update it last with partition=0. After each pod comes back up, I'll check the replica set health and make sure everything's stable before proceeding. Once all three are running 6.0, I'll update the feature compatibility version and repeat the same process for 7.0, though I should note that mongo 6.0+ uses `mongosh` instead of the older `mongo` CLI. update image to mongo:6.0\n\nStep 2: Wait for pod-2 to be ready and verify it's a healthy secondary\n\nStep 3: Set partition=1 to roll pod-1\n\nStep 4: Wait for pod-1 to be ready and verify it's a healthy secondary\n\nStep 5: Step down the primary (pod-0) so we can upgrade it last\n\nStep 6: Set partition=0 to roll pod-0\n\nStep 7: Wait for pod-0 to be ready and verify the replica set health\n\nStep 8: Set FCV to 6.0 on the new primary\n\nThen I'll repeat the same rolling update process for MongoDB 7.0 using the mongo:7.0.5 image.\n\nNow I need to execute this plan. I should keep in mind that mongo:6.0 uses mongosh instead of the mongo client, so I'll need to adjust the commands accordingly as I work through each pod.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":980,"cache_read_input_tokens":38670,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":980},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ba695925-cd8d-4d1b-ba62-01ff90735b20","uuid":"b9159282-66b1-481b-872a-00689acf02fa","request_id":"req_011CbxL4aMhToL6T61stErPt"}
